  <h2>Scenario 1 - Simplicity &amp; Standings Context</h2>

  <p><strong>Persona:</strong> Casual Football Fan</p>
  <p><strong>Profile:</strong> Watches PSL matches occasionally, mainly follows their favorite team. Not a heavy bettor but likes checking fixtures and standings to keep track of performance.</p>
  <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Test whether the dashboard's clean layout helps users quickly find upcoming matches, and if they feel they have enough contextual information (like team positions in the league table) before deciding to place a bet.</p>
  


  <h3>Observations</h3>
  <p> At least 2 users added that they would like to have the standings table for the current season to be present on their dashboard as they log in
   so that they can quickly see each team's postion in the league up until the present</p>

  <h3>Quotes</h3>
  <blockquote>
    "The page is very neat. But honestly, I wouldn't bet without knowing where my team is on the table."
  </blockquote>

  <h3>Pain Points</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Lack of standings context disrupted the betting decision.</li>
    <li>Extra step (opening another site) created frustration.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Design Change</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Added the PSL League Standings Table beneath the upcoming matches section.</li>
    <li>Highlighted key metrics (Matches Played, Wins, GD, Points).</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Outcome</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Positive feedback on visual clarity of standings integration.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8" />

  <h2>Scenario 2 - Recent Match Results for Form</h2>

  <p><strong>Persona:</strong> Regular Bettor</p>
  <p><strong>Profile:</strong> Places bets weekly. Knows PSL teams well. Makes decisions based on form and recent scores, not just fixtures.</p>
  <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Evaluate whether users want Recent Match Results on the same page as fixtures to better judge form and make more confident bets.</p>
  

  <h3>Observations</h3>
  <p> Users interested in the betting side of the website were frustrated with that fact that they would
   have to open a new tab to see recent match results so they could see if there were any matches like landslide victories or curshing defeats
   that are out of the ordinary for a particular team that might influence their betting decision  </p>

  <h3>Quotes</h3>
  <blockquote>
    "If I can see the last 3-5 results right here, I don't need to Google anything. That speeds me up a lot."
  </blockquote>

  <h3>Pain Point</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Context switching to external sites to see recent matches.</li>
    
  </ul>

  <h3>Design Change</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Added Recent Match Results panel.</li>
    <li>Simple layout: Match | Score | Date, with stadium as subtext.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Outcome</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Positive sentiment: bettors felt "everything they needed" was on one page.</li>
  </ul>

