  <h2>Scenario 3 - Emphasis on Date/Time &amp; Venue near "Bet Now"</h2>

  <p><strong>Persona:</strong> New Betting User</p>
  <p><strong>Profile:</strong> First-time dashboard user, not deeply familiar with teams or stadiums. Relies heavily on interface clarity to avoid mistakes.</p>
  <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Ensure users can clearly see kick-off time and venue before pressing Bet Now, reducing the chance of accidental or misplaced bets.</p>
  <h3>Tasks</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Identify a match that fits your schedule.</li>
    <li>Before betting, read aloud the time and venue.</li>
    <li>Place the bet.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Observations</h3>
  We noticed when asking user that have little to no experience that felt rushed by the "Bet Now" button for each specific 
  upcoming match so they wanted to bet right away without first looking at more information like the statistics, standings table and 
  recent results tables
  </ul>

  <h3>Quotes</h3>
  <blockquote>
    "I almost clicked Bet straight away. Having the time right above the button makes me double-check."
  </blockquote>

  <h3>Pain Points</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Important context (time &amp; venue) felt secondary to the action button.</li>
    <li>Inconsistent positioning of info across cards caused scanning friction.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Design Change</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Standardized match cards: Time &amp; Venue now appear immediately above Bet Now.</li>
    <li>Increased contrast for time; stadium shown in muted but fixed position.</li>
    <li>Added "Scheduled" chip to reinforce non-live status.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Outcome</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Users felt less "forced" to make a bet immediately.</li>
  </ul>

